Also, the very threat of nukes will deter both sides from increasing the intensity of any skirmish beyond the level of a small border war.<br>
Taking that into account, the border war will probably have gains and losses on both sides but eventually end in a stalemate.<br>
The Indian troops are better armed and prepared/trained then they were back in 1962. The Chinese do not hold a numericaly advantage as they did in '62. Overall, neither side has the sort of advantage to make the war a clear victory or loss.<br>
